text.tspan: Storyboard of freelance translator, Nancy’s, journey to start accessing app ‘Listicle’
This is Nancy, 32 years old, a freelance translator and writer.
Gets translation work from U.K. clients and a few from abroad.
A task-management app used by users who need to manage and organise themselves at work.
Nancy checks out the features of ‘Checklist’
She is from Britain. Delivering projects on time and being punctual is
appreciated by her national and international clients.
Downloads it on her desktop and gives a first try
Her frustrations: Number of projects are increasing and she would like to
have sources by which she can remember deadlines and stay organised.
Starts using the app and feels she is able to manage daily tasks smartly

text.data-name: Meet Nancy, she 32 years old. A freelance translator. She gets a lot translation work and looks for ways to keep herself organised.

She is from Britain.
Work culture: punctuality
Handles national and international clients

Has a lot content projects to manage.
Wants to meet deadlines.
Likes to schedule her projects and stay ahead.

She goes on the online app store and checks out ‘Listicle’ app.
Nancy checks out the features in the tutorial:
text.tspan: She goes on the online app

text.data-name: A basic app where I can see not just ‘to-do’ list but also translations done
text.tspan: A basic app where I can see

text.data-name: Downloads the app and starts using to get a feel of the navigation

I’m happy using this app. More organised. I open the app to check out my ‘to-do’ tasks daily. Prioritise and mark the completed ones. A smart way to organise myself rather than noting down on a piece of paper or using complicated, cumbersome apps.
